# GOVs-AI — AI-Powered Government Scheme Eligibility Platform

A startup-ready SaaS platform that uses an autonomous AI agent to help Indian citizens discover, evaluate, and apply for government welfare schemes through intelligent conversational profiling, RAG-powered document retrieval, and personalized eligibility analysis.

---

## Scope & Feasibility Strategy

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This is a **hackathon MVP** — not a production deployment. The plan prioritizes **demonstrable AI agent capabilities** (Planning, Tool Usage, Memory, Autonomous Execution) and **visual polish** over exhaustive backend infrastructure. Components like Redis, PostgreSQL, Celery, and role-based admin are **simplified** to keep the build feasible.

### MVP Architecture Decision

| Concern | Production Ideal | Hackathon MVP (Our Choice) |
|---|---|---|
| Database | PostgreSQL + migrations | SQLite via SQLAlchemy (zero-config, portable) |
| Memory | Redis + LangGraph Checkpointer | In-memory dict + JSON file persistence |
| Task Queue | Celery + Redis broker | FastAPI BackgroundTasks |
| Auth | OAuth2 + JWT + refresh tokens | JWT with bcrypt hashing (simplified) |
| Vector Store | Pinecone / Weaviate | FAISS (local, zero-cost) |
| Deployment | Docker + K8s | Local dev servers |

